COMPLETENESS REQUIREMENT

Return exactly one theme_mappings entry for each theme in WS_THEME_DICTIONARY_JSON.

Do not omit dictionary themes.
Do not add extra themes.

QUALITY STANDARD

The output should be conservative, precise, and suitable for machine use.

Avoid advocacy language.
Avoid dramatic language.
Avoid generic labels unless they are already in the controlled dictionary.
Every PRESENT or LATENT mapping must have a clear WS evidence anchor.
Every ABSENT mapping should have an empty ws_evidence_anchors array.
Every RISK_ONLY mapping should explain the duplication, speculation, overreach, or evidential risk.
Use at most one ws_evidence_anchors item per theme.
Keep anchor_summary, short_quote_or_paraphrase, duplication_risk, and mapping_rationale to one concise sentence each.
Keep short_quote_or_paraphrase under 25 words.

VALIDATION REQUIREMENTS

Before returning the JSON, internally check:

1. Every mapped_theme_id exists in WS_THEME_DICTIONARY_JSON.
2. No new theme_id or theme_name has been created.
3. theme_priority values match WS_THEME_DICTIONARY_JSON.
4. recommended_action values are permitted for the mapped theme.
5. cross_reference_theme_ids contain only valid dictionary theme_ids.
6. cross_reference_theme_ids do not include the mapped_theme_id.
7. No WS text has been rewritten.
8. No new allegation has been created.
9. No external law has been used.
10. The JSON contains exactly one theme_mappings entry for each dictionary theme.

Return JSON only.
